CIA Triad + Security Controls (Linux ACLs)

This lab demonstrates how to enforce the CIA triad using Linux file permissions and ACLs, simulate access violations, and detect them using auditd â€” just like in a real SOC.

Topics Covered
- CIA Triad (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)
- Security Controls (Administrative, Technical, Physical)
- Linux ACLs
- File access violation simulation
- auditd for detection

Tools Used
- Linux (Ubuntu)
- auditd
- setfacl / getfacl
